Definition: a form of schizophrenia characterized by a tendency to remain in a fixed stuporous state for long periods
Example: the catatonia may give way to short periods of extreme excitement
Synonyms: catatonic_type_schizophrenia, catatonia, adj, pert, catatonic, schizophrenia, a, form, of, characterized, by, tendency, to, remain, in, fixed, stuporous, state, for, long, periods, the, may, give, way, short, extreme, excitement
Category: noun.state
